The UNITED STATES of America ex rel. James MICHAEL, Petitioner-Appellant, v. Joseph E. RAGEN, Warden, Illinois State Penitentiary, Respondent-Appellee. No. 6690. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Aug. 30, 1938.

Before SPARKS and MAJOR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is now here ordered and adjudged that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
